This program will reverse the nodes in the even position of a single link list.

EXAMPLE:
--------
I/P: 1-2-3-4-5-6-7-8
O/P: 1-8-3-6-5-4-7-2

HOW TO COMPILE & BUILD THE EXECUTABLE:
--------------------------------------
1) Checkout the "LL_Even_Node_Reversal" directory and do not change the directory structure or name of directories present inside this directory.
2) Go inside "make" directory and give "make -f make_LL_rev_even_node". This will generate object file into "LL_Even_Node_Reversal/obj"
directory and executable will be generated inside "LL_Even_Node_Reversal/bin" directory.
3) Executable name is "reverse_even_node".
4) Give executable permission to the "reverse_even_node" file generated in "LL_Even_Node_Reversal/bin". (chmod +
x ip_addr_to_bin)
5) If you want to remove the object files and executables, then go inside "LL_Even_Node_Reversal/make" and gi
ve "make -f make_LL_rev_even_node clean". Now, give "make -f make_LL_rev_even_node" to compile and generate the executable again.


HOW TO RUN:
----------
1) Go inside "LL_Even_Node_Reversal/bin".
2) ./reverse_even_node
3) Enter the total number of nodes you want to insert in the linked list & then enter an integer value for that many nodes.

SAMPLE OUTPUTS:
--------------
OUTPUT1:
--------
./reverse_even_node 
Enter the total Number of nodes:8

Enter the Node-1 data:1

Enter the Node-2 data:2

Enter the Node-3 data:3

Enter the Node-4 data:4

Enter the Node-5 data:5

Enter the Node-6 data:6

Enter the Node-7 data:7

Enter the Node-8 data:8

Output of the sorted list:
 The data stored in the list are: 1 8 3 6 5 4 7 2

=============================================================
